annotationA: Histone-like protein 18C; Not known. Encoded in the intron of cAMP-dependent protein kinase regulatory chain type I
annotationB: Cytochrome c-1; Electron carrier protein. The oxidized form of the cytochrome c heme group can accept an electron from the heme group of the cytochrome c1 subunit of cytochrome reductase. Cytochrome c then transfers this electron to the cytochrome oxidase complex, the final protein carrier in the mitochondrial electron-transport chain
